    <h4 class="myheadings">Upscaling &gt;&gt;</h4>
    <div class="thecontent">
    <table border="1" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="10" width="100%">
        <tr>
          <td class="incompatible">RX-V375</td>
          <td class="incompatible">RX-V475</td>
          <td class="incompatible">RX-V500D</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td class="incompatible">RX-V575</td>
          <td class="compatible">RX-V675</td>
          <td class="compatible">RX-V775</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td class="compatible">RX-V1075</td>
          <td class="compatible">RX-V2073</td>
          <td class="compatible">RX-V3073</td>
        </tr>
      </table>
      <br>
      <p>Upscaling enhances the resolution of lower-quality images by adding information to ensure all pixels on the television are used. When upscaled to 1080p, DVD sources appear as close to Blu-ray quality as possible.</p>
      <p>Yamaha’s RX-V675 and above are able to upscale images to the new standard of 4K ultra high-definition.</p>
      <p><img src="images/upscaling.jpg" width="100%" alt="Upscaling"></p>
    </div>
